HEADWORD: Duotone
<hw>Du"o*tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>duo</ets>
two + <ets>tone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Photoengraving)</fld> <def>Any
picture printed in two shades of the same color, as duotypes and
duographs are usually printed.</def>⟦br⟧
